Package androidx.swiperefreshlayout.widget

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SwipeRefreshLayout.OnChildScrollUpCallback
    Classes that wish to override SwipeRefreshLayout.canChildScrollUp() method behavior should implement this interface.
    SwipeRefreshLayout.OnRefreshListener
    Classes that wish to be notified when the swipe gesture correctly triggers a refresh should implement this interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CircularProgressDrawable
    Drawable that renders the animated indeterminate progress indicator in the Material design style without depending on API level 11.
    SwipeRefreshLayout
    The SwipeRefreshLayout should be used whenever the user can refresh the contents of a view via a vertical swipe gesture.

    Annotation Type Description
    CircularProgressDrawable.ProgressDrawableSize

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
